name: df-xpc
params: setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, setvar s4, setvar s5, setvar s6, setvar s7, setvar s8, setvar s9
body: |- wceq(cxpc, cmpo(s0, s1, universe, universe, csb(s2, cxp(cfv(cbs, cv(s0)), cfv(cbs, cv(s1))), csb(s5, cmpo(s3, s4, cv(s2), cv(s2), cxp(co(cfv(c1st, cv(s3)), cfv(chom, cv(s0)), cfv(c1st, cv(s4))), co(cfv(c2nd, cv(s3)), cfv(chom, cv(s1)), cfv(c2nd, cv(s4))))), ctp(cop(cfv(cbs, cnx), cv(s2)), cop(cfv(chom, cnx), cv(s5)), cop(cfv(cco, cnx), cmpo(s6, s7, cxp(cv(s2), cv(s2)), cv(s2), cmpo(s8, s9, co(cfv(c2nd, cv(s6)), cv(s5), cv(s7)), cfv(cv(s5), cv(s6)), cop(co(cfv(c1st, cv(s8)), co(cop(cfv(c1st, cfv(c1st, cv(s6))), cfv(c1st, cfv(c2nd, cv(s6)))), cfv(cco, cv(s0)), cfv(c1st, cv(s7))), cfv(c1st, cv(s9))), co(cfv(c2nd, cv(s8)), co(cop(cfv(c2nd, cfv(c1st, cv(s6))), cfv(c2nd, cfv(c2nd, cv(s6)))), cfv(cco, cv(s1)), cfv(c2nd, cv(s7))), cfv(c2nd, cv(s9))))))))))))
comment: Define the binary product of categories, which has objects for each pair of objects of the factors, and morphisms for each pair of morphisms of the factors. Composition is componentwise. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 10-Jan-2017.)
